SLS 26RS-676 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 14
BY SENATOR HODGES AND REPRESENTATIVE DICKERSON
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH. Designates the month of March 2026, as "Flood
Awareness Month" in Louisiana and commends the invaluable contributions of all the
professionals who are working everyday to protect lives, homes, businesses, and
communities from floods.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To designate the month of March 2026, as "Flood Awareness Month" in Louisiana and to
3 commend the invaluable contributions of all professionals working every day to
4 protect lives, homes, businesses, and communities from floods.
5 WHEREAS, the state of Louisiana recognizes that floods are among the most
6 common natural hazards in the United States and can occur any time, threatening life,
7 property, and the economy; and
8 WHEREAS, approximately ninety percent of all natural disasters in the United States
9 involve flooding; and
10 WHEREAS, flooding represents Louisiana's prevalent and pervasive natural disaster
11 threat which poses significant risks throughout the state; and
12 WHEREAS, not all floods are alike, as some develop slowly, while others, such as
13 flash floods, can develop within minutes and without visible signs of rain; and
14 WHEREAS, overland flooding, the most common type of flooding event, typically
15 occurs when waterways such as rivers and streams overflow their banks due to excessive
16 rainfall or possible levee breaches causing flooding in surrounding areas, and may also occur
17 when rainfall exceeds the capacity of underground pipes, streets, and drainage systems
18 designed to carry flood waters away from urban areas; and
