1 and the overall vitality of society depend, in large measure, upon the dedication of the hard
2 working professionals in the flood protection and storm water management industry who use
3 their talents to strengthen public infrastructure and improve resilience and safety each day
4 and in times of disaster; and
5 WHEREAS, Flood Awareness Month provides an opportunity to raise awareness
6 about the importance of flood preparedness and to encourage all citizens to better prepare
7 their homes, businesses, and communities.
8 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
9 designate the month of March 2026, as "Flood Awareness Month" in Louisiana and does
10 hereby commend the invaluable contributions of all the professionals, who are working
11 everyday in the flood protection and storm water management industry, to protect lives,
12 homes, businesses, and communities from flooding.
13 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
14 president of the Amite River Basin Board of Commissioners.
